  <section class="faq-section"><div class="container">
    <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">FAQs</span><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><p>Common questions about lounge access credit cards</p></div>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">How do I access a lounge with my credit card?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Simply walk to any participating lounge at the airport, present your credit card (or Priority Pass card if issued separately) along with a valid boarding pass for a same-day flight. The lounge staff will verify your card's eligibility and grant access. For domestic lounges via Dreamfolks, some banks require you to generate a lounge access code through the banking app before visiting. Always check which lounges are covered by your card's specific program — Priority Pass, Dreamfolks, and card network lounges each have different participating locations.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Can I bring guests to the airport lounge?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">It depends on your card. Premium cards like HDFC Infinia allow you to bring guests at a discounted rate or sometimes for free. Most cards charge $27-$35 (₹2,200-₹2,900) per guest visit which gets billed to your credit card. Some cards include a specific number of complimentary guest visits per year. Children under 2 years are typically free, and children between 2-12 may be charged at a reduced rate. Check your card's lounge access terms for the exact guest policy.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">What is the difference between Priority Pass and Dreamfolks?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Priority Pass is a global lounge access program with 1,300+ lounges in 600+ cities across 150+ countries — ideal for international travellers. Dreamfolks is an India-focused program providing access to 50+ domestic airport lounges, railway station lounges, and spa services. Many cards include both programs. Priority Pass is better for international travel, while Dreamfolks offers more extensive coverage at Indian domestic airports. Super-premium cards typically include both, giving you comprehensive coverage everywhere you fly.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Do lounge visits reset every year or quarter?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">It varies by card. HDFC cards typically reset lounge visits at the beginning of each calendar quarter (e.g., 2 per quarter = 8 per year). Axis cards usually provide an annual quota (e.g., 8 per year). SBI cards follow a membership year (12 months from card issuance). Unlimited access cards like HDFC Infinia and Diners Black have no limits regardless of period. Always verify your specific card's reset cycle in the card's terms document or banking app to plan your lounge usage effectively.</div></div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-question">Can I get lounge access with a lifetime free card?<i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></button><div class="faq-answer"><div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes! The IDFC First WOW card is a lifetime free card that includes 4 complimentary domestic lounge visits per year. The AU Small Finance Lit Card (also LTF) offers lounge access as well. While these are limited compared to premium paid cards, getting any lounge access with a zero-fee card is exceptional value. Each free visit saves you ₹1,500-₹2,000, meaning 4 visits provide ₹6,000-₹8,000 in annual value without paying a rupee in card fees.</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div></section>

